# Pre-Deploy Accounts Checklist

Every external service you need to register with **before** running
`infra/DEPLOY.md`. Times are realistic active time. Save each credential
into a password manager or a temporary `secrets.txt` you'll feed into
`gcloud secrets versions add` (DEPLOY.md §3.6).

This template is the structure that worked for a real production rollout
— 9 services, ordered by deploy-blocking status. Edit the list to match
the services your project actually uses; keep the format (For / URL /
Time / Steps / Save / Cost / Skip-OK) for each entry so the table at the
bottom stays accurate.

---

## 1. GitHub
**For:** code repo + CI/CD via GitHub Actions
**URL:** https://github.com
**Required:** admin rights on the repo so you can set Actions secrets and
variables in DEPLOY.md §5.2.
**Save:** nothing new.
**Cost:** free.

---

## 2. Google Cloud Platform
**For:** runs the entire service (Cloud Run, Cloud SQL, GCS, Tasks,
Scheduler, Secret Manager)
**URL:** https://console.cloud.google.com/
**Time:** 15 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign in with a Google account (Workspace or personal).
2. Create a new project → save the **Project ID** (not the name).
3. **Enable billing.** Billing → Link a billing account → add a credit
   card. Without this every `gcloud` command fails. New accounts get $300
   free credit good for 90 days.
4. Install `gcloud` CLI locally: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
5. `gcloud auth login` and `gcloud config set project <PROJECT_ID>`

**Save:** `PROJECT_ID`
**Cost:** ~$9/month fixed (mostly Cloud SQL micro instance) once the
trial credit runs out.

---

## 3. Primary identity provider (e.g., Telegram BotFather, Auth0, Clerk, Cognito)
**For:** the authentication front-door for your users
**URL:** depends on provider
**Time:** 3–15 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign up / create an app or bot.
2. Configure the redirect/webhook URL placeholder — you'll replace it with
   your Cloud Run URL after first deploy.
3. Copy the application secret / bot token.
4. Generate a webhook secret locally if your provider supports one:
   `openssl rand -hex 32`. Save it.

**Save:**
- `AUTH_PROVIDER_TOKEN` (or `BOT_TOKEN` / `CLIENT_SECRET` / etc.)
- `AUTH_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (if applicable)

**Cost:** usually free at low volume.

---

## 4. Primary ML / AI provider (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, Gemini, AWS Bedrock)
**For:** the main inference call (transcription, summarization, generation
— whatever this product does)
**URL:** depends on provider
**Time:** 5 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign up.
2. Console → API Keys → Create API Key → name it
   `{{PROJECT_NAME}}-prod`.
3. Copy immediately — most providers do not show the key again.

**Save:** `LLM_API_KEY`
**Cost:** pay-per-token usually; budget for $0.01–$0.10 per request
depending on model + length.

---

## 5. Secondary / fallback ML provider (optional but recommended)
**For:** A/B testing and fallback when the primary provider has an outage
**URL:** depends on provider
**Time:** 3 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign in (often the same Google / Microsoft account as your primary
   cloud — simplifies billing).
2. Create API key → copy it.

**Save:** `LLM_FALLBACK_API_KEY`
**Cost:** usually has a free tier sufficient for fallback duty.
**Skip-OK:** yes for Phase 1, no for Phase 3+.

---

## 6. Stripe (or Paddle / LemonSqueezy / Chargebee)
**For:** subscription billing
**URL:** https://dashboard.stripe.com/register
**Time:** 30–60 min (the longest because of identity verification)
**Steps:**
1. Sign up. Pick your country and business type. **Use a real legal
   entity** — Stripe will ask for it.
2. **Activate your account.** Business name, address, tax ID/SSN, and a
   bank account for payouts. Verification can take a few hours to a day.
3. Until activated, you can still build with **Test mode** keys. Start
   the deploy with test keys, switch to live keys after activation.
4. **Developers → API keys:**
   - Test mode: copy `sk_test_...` for `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` (use for
     initial deploy).
   - Live mode: rotate to `sk_live_...` after activation.
5. **Products → Add product:** create your subscription tiers (e.g., Solo
   / Team / Enterprise). Save each `price_xxx` ID.
6. **Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint** — skip this until after the
   first Cloud Run deploy. You need a real URL. (See DEPLOY.md §8.2.)
7. The webhook signing secret (`whsec_...`) is shown **once** when you
   create the endpoint. Save it then.

**Save:**
- `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` (start with test key)
- `STRIPE_PRICE_<TIER>_MO` (one per subscription tier)
- `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (after the webhook is created post-deploy)

**Cost:** 2.9% + 30¢ per successful charge. No monthly fee.
**Skip-OK:** yes if you're not charging users yet — drop this section in
Phase 1.

---

## 7. Sentry — recommended
**For:** real-time alerts when production breaks
**URL:** https://sentry.io/signup/
**Time:** 5 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign up. Free tier is 5k events/month — enough for Phase 1.
2. Create organization → create a new project → Platform: **Python /
   FastAPI** → name it `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`.
3. Sentry shows you a DSN like
   `https://abc...@o123.ingest.sentry.io/456`. Copy it.
4. (Optional) Set up Slack/email alerts under Alerts → Issue Alert rules.

**Save:** `SENTRY_DSN`
**Cost:** free tier.
**Skip-OK:** yes. Set the secret to an empty string if you skip (DEPLOY.md
§3.7).

---

## 8. PostHog (or Mixpanel / Amplitude) — optional
**For:** product analytics (funnel, retention, % of users who pay,
average jobs per user)
**URL:** https://app.posthog.com/signup
**Time:** 5 min
**Steps:**
1. Sign up. EU or US data residency — pick based on your users' location.
2. Create a project → name it `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`.
3. Project settings → Project API key — copy it.

**Save:** `POSTHOG_API_KEY`, `POSTHOG_HOST` (defaults to
`https://us.posthog.com`)
**Cost:** 1M events/month free.
**Skip-OK:** yes. Leave the secret empty.

---

## 9. Domain registrar — optional
**For:** vanity URL instead of
`https://{{PROJECT_NAME}}-abc123-ew.a.run.app`
**URLs:**
- https://domains.google (now Gandi)
- https://cloudflare.com/products/registrar (cheapest, at-cost pricing)
- https://www.namecheap.com

**Time:** 10 min + DNS propagation wait
**Steps:**
1. Buy a domain.
2. After Cloud Run is deployed, map the domain via Cloud Run → Custom
   Domains → Add mapping. Cloud Run gives you DNS records to add at your
   registrar.

**Cost:** $10–$15/year.
**Skip-OK:** yes — the Cloud Run URL works fine for most webhook
integrations.

---

## Order of operations (compressed)

| Step | Service | Blocks deploy? | Active time |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | GitHub admin access | Yes | 0 min |
| 2 | GCP project + billing | Yes | 15 min |
| 3 | Primary identity provider | Yes | 3–15 min |
| 4 | Primary ML provider | Yes | 5 min |
| 5 | Fallback ML provider | No (Phase 1) | 3 min |
| 6 | Stripe (test keys + products) | Yes, for billing flows | 30 min (+ verification wait) |
| 7 | Sentry DSN | No | 5 min |
| 8 | PostHog API key | No | 5 min |
| 9 | Custom domain | No | 10 min + DNS wait |

**Total active time:** ~75 min if you do everything. Start Stripe first —
their identity verification can add up to a business day in the
background.

---

## Quick credential checklist

Paste this template into a temporary `secrets.txt` and fill it in as you
go (edit to match the secrets your `cloud_run.yaml` actually references):

```
PROJECT_ID=
AUTH_PROVIDER_TOKEN=
AUTH_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
LLM_API_KEY=
LLM_FALLBACK_API_KEY=
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_PRICE_SOLO_MO=
STRIPE_PRICE_TEAM_MO=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=   # filled in after first deploy
SENTRY_DSN=              # optional
POSTHOG_API_KEY=         # optional
CRON_SECRET=             # generate locally: openssl rand -hex 32
```

Once filled, you can run DEPLOY.md §3.6 in one sitting and feed every
secret into Secret Manager.

**Delete `secrets.txt` immediately after** — those values should only ever
live in Secret Manager once deployed.
